Brenan's heard jerked up from the holy book in which his head had been burried in in meditation.  He heard a noise.  A voice, but not one belonging to friend of his.  It was desperate.....faint from the distance.  But, yes, he managed to make out two words, bard, and trouble.  Or....barb and bubble, but that just didn't make sense, did it.  No, Paren was in trouble.  When wasn't he...Rising to his feet, Brenan ran.  The voice was distant still, but growing louder as his feet pounded against the hard ground.  Louder, louder.  The sound of dying kobolds echoed throughout the area.  The screams of their dead were worse than the sound of the Maestro residing in Hate, or so he had been told.  Paren!  His body lay sprawled on ground, a Kerran staunchly standing defending him.  Without ceremony, a distraught but ever serious cleric knelt down beside his bardic friend.  Two fingers pressed against a wrist growing cold.  Seconds passed before Brenan felt a pulse, and a weak pulse it was.  But he was alive, and thats all he needed.  Brenan bared his soul to Rodcet Nife, begging life for the bard whose cause was just and spirit even more kind.  The healing light of a god bathed the pair in its radiance.  Brenan's eyelids fluttered as he used part of his own life to repair that which was damaged in his friends.  He felt weak, as if his insides would slip out of his body and his muscles would fail him.  The skin beneath his fingers grew warmer and blood began to flow, as Brenan's skin began to pail and his blood slow its pace.  Using Raiki, a form of healing using ones own body heat to heal another, he finished his work.  Eye lids shut as Brenan told himself the only thing Paren would need is sleep.  The thing Brenan needed himself was a warm bed, and sleep, forever sleep.  Hopefully that Kerran can hold at bay those kobolds, hopefully. <p>Ignis Summa Pugnabat, The fires shall cleanse the world.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left>