ng again Yavi pulled the woodelf closer to him. &quot;Hush your tongue young one, we do not know these people, they may not be as understanding as I, or my sect to your kind.&quot; A discuraged look came over her face and she wrapped her arms around the warriors waist.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rillen@fantasystoriesforum>Rillen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Weaver of Flames</span><br>  Posts: 282<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/14/02 6:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Adventures of Rillen and the Gang</span><hr size=1> OOC (Everythings going along wonderfully.  I'm really interested in how your playing two charecters Bonaki, I've myself tried it in a previous RP with little success.  So far, your skill at it has caused no confusion whatsoever and writing excelently.  Just a question, maybe I missed it, I know the clerics a wood elf, can I assume the warrior is the same?)  <br>
