<br>
Forna rambled on through the forest. The dead foliage snapped beneath her graceful, yet powerful steps. She was on her way to meet up with Bren, Hoku, and Paren. A few weeks ago, Forna had received a letter calling her away from her friends. It was a letter from her father. Family matters, right? Wrong. It wasn't a letter saying, &quot;Dear, Aunt Laurel just died. Come home.&quot; No, it was business. He needed her. The man who taught her all she knows about being a physical weapon needed HER. The novice. Well, she wasn't a novice anymore.<br>
<br>
Kicking a rock ahead of her, Forna cursed to herself. She should have never went to see him. Being as advanced in sensory as she was, she should have KNOWN it was going to be bad. Yeah, he was her father, she wanted to help him, but she didn't want this...<br>
<br>
The sheathing of a sword caught Forna's ear, stopping, she crouched low and surveyed the area. Music began to lace through the trees and dance in her ears, followed by corny lyrics, that needed grand amounts of work. A smile illuminated her face, and brightened her sky blue eyes. Standing erect again she began to run towards the music, it was Paren, it had to be, and where Paren was, so were the others.<br>
<br>
It was time to push down her troubles, she would talk to Bren about it later. Now was the time to rejoin her friends, her family. <br>
<br>
Dashing past the trees, she caught the glint of armor, the warmth radianting from her friends, but she could sense others. As Forna stepped before her friends, she stopped, her foot coming down on a twig that emitted a loud snap to reverberate in her ears and the group before her. The crowd grew silent for a split second, as Forna's conscience was screaming about the letter, but she pushed it down.<br>
<br>
A bright smile crossed her features, as she jumped and hugged Paren, tackling him to the ground, &quot;Paren! You crazy Bard! How you doing!?&quot; She ruffled his hair then jumped to her feet, as she looked around to everyone they didn't seem so chipper... Looking to Hoku, she gave a little wave, then just stopped, there was a man and a young elven girl she had never seen in her life, not to mention the fur ball eyeing her down. Forna's blue eyes found Bren, her eyebrow shifting to an arch, &quot;Did someone die? Or are you all just THIS excited to see me?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ryvian>Ryvian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warlord of Delnor</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/16/02 2:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks!</span><hr size=1> Being taken to the ground, Paren smiled but nearly lost his jig. &quot;Forna, darlin' could you ease up just a tad? I'm not totally fixed just yet.&quot; His ribs, that never fully healed were throbbing. Smiling again, Paren tried to stand up. &quot;Damn it's been too long! Where'd ya go off to so quickly like that? I'm sure it was important, why would anyone want to leave such a wonderful bard as myself for anything other than the most important deeds?&quot; His smile faded when his eyes met Hoku, &quot;Ok so maybe I'm not the best bard ever, but hell I'm pretty close.&quot; Looking back to his riend Forna, &quot;Darlin' these two are travelers. Yavi the warrior, and Amy the cleric.&quot; Paren pointed them out. &quot;We were just having a little chat about understanding. Weren't we buddy?&quot; Paren asked Bren. Not waiting for a response Paren quickly turned back to Forna. &quot;So where'd ya go this time? Get me anything?&quot; Looking back to Hoku's huff, Paren backed off just a little. &quot;Ok well now that most of us know each other, umm.. the furry guy is still a stranger to us.&quot; Paren turned again. &quot;I'm Paren, a bard. You know, sing sing sing.&quot; Paren made little singing noises and spoke very slowly. Looking at all the unamused faces Paren gave a sigh. No humor, these where is the fun! &quot;Fine let's just go and grab some food, I'm starved.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=12.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=12.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=12.topic&start=61&stop=78>4</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showNextMessage?topicID=12.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=40><img src=http://Auction.2y.net/user/paradisetheheretic/addreply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.emailToFriend?topicID=12.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.threadControl?topicID=12.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=12.top